=====================================================
Chapel Compiler Release Directory Structure and Files
=====================================================

The following list gives an overview of $CHPL_HOME's structure.
Several subdirectories contain files named README to further describe
the files and directories that they contain.

./
  README            : top-level README with quick-start information
  README.files      : this file
  BUILD_VERSION     : the build version since the last minor version update
  CONTRIBUTORS      : a list of contributors to the Chapel project
  COPYRIGHT         : copyright information
  LICENSE           : Chapel's license
  STATUS            : a list of unimplemented features and bugs
  Makefile          : top-level Makefile for building the compiler and runtime
  bin/
    $CHPL_PLATFORM/ : location of compiler, chpl, after it has been built
  compiler/         : compiler sources
  doc/              : documentation
  examples/         : example Chapel codes
    hpcc06/         : source code for 2006 HPC Challenge competition
  lib/
    $CHPL_PLATFORM/ : runtime library location, once they've been built
  make/             : Makefile settings for various platforms
  modules/          : standard Chapel modules
  runtime/          : source files for Chapel's runtime support libraries
    etc/            : Makefiles for compiler-generated code
    include/        : header files for runtime support libraries
    src/            : source code for runtime support libraries
  util/             : utility scripts
